	measure 'Margin Definitions' = ```
			
			"-Netbacks (defined as Net sales, less cost to serve) -  Net sales is the gross revenue, net of rebates and other discounts and Cost to serve is the freight and handling cost incurred to deliver the product to the customer." 
			& UNICHAR(10) & 
			"-Variable Margin (defined as netback, less variable mfg. cost) -also referred to as Contribution Margin, represents the incremental dollars generated from selling an incremental unit of product." 
			& UNICHAR(10) &
			"-Gross Cash Margin (defined as Variable Margin, less fixed cash operating costs) – represents how much of the contribution or variable margin is left after covering fixed opex costs."
			```
		displayFolder: 0-Base Measures
		lineageTag: 1ac97701-ed8f-40c4-a545-67551748a5f5

		annotation PBI_FormatHint = {"isGeneralNumber":true}

